benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: Valid Request: The suite includes multiple successful retrieval scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC08, TC09) covering required accountId and various query parameters.
Empty Response: Scenarios TC06 and TC07 verify empty results when there are no custom fields or no matching objectType.
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of objectType and audit parameters, including combinations and edge cases (TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC31, TC32, TC36).
Authorization: Tests for missing authentication and invalid tokens (TC14, TC15).
Input Validation & Edge Cases: Validation scenarios for accountId formats and content (TC12, TC33-35) and whitespace handling in objectType (TC36) plus basic XSS/SQL injection checks (TC17, TC18).
Security/Resilience: Includes regression tests and recovery scenarios (TC21, TC22, TC23, TC24, TC39) and accessibility checks (TC37, TC38).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for pagination of results when there are many custom fields.
Rate Limiting: No tests validating throttling or 429 responses under rapid request load.
Caching Behavior: No tests asserting caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache invalidation.
Authorization nuances: Only 401 asserted; no test covering 403 Forbidden for insufficient permissions.
Server Errors: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario; only 503-based service outage tests.
recommendations: Add pagination tests to ensure correct behavior (page size, page tokens, total counts) when accounts have large numbers of custom fields.
Add rate limiting tests to verify system behavior under high request load and ensure proper 429 responses if configured.
Add caching tests to verify presence and correctness of cache headers, ETag validation, and cache-control directives.
Extend authorization tests to include 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover insufficient permissions.
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario simulations to verify server-side failure handling.
